<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100389388046050></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100389388046050><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=1875&mid=100389388046050>Got my mask as a level 3 rogue...</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=1875&mid=100389388046050#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=104804><span id= >Spectix</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>19 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Oct 23rd 11:24 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>&nbsp;&nbsp;   Ok as far as I'm concerned this mask is a must have for Barbarian Rogues. Why? Well first of all Barbarians lack of night vision is very frustrating and annoying. Second of all it allows you to get into the evil alligned cities (except for Cabalis of course). And third, Dark Elves have hands down the sweetest looking armor out of any race. Ever see a Dark Elf in full Ry'Gorr? Looks phat as hell. Ok well anyway heres how I got mine: I got a kind Wizard to TL me to N ro, then I ran invisible to Lguk (Normal frogloks should be dubious btw). Then I used Sneak + Hide to get past the frogluks in the entrance. However, it is not possible to get out of the water sneaking + hiding unless you are SoWed. The solution: wait or ask for someone to clear out the bedroom. You can quick hop out of the water then re-sneak and re-hide. Then the rest is just a matter of sneaking and hiding into the assasin's room if he isn't up (he sees through sneak + hide). You can camp your little Rogue in the room until someone goes after the Assasin or whatever. In my experience he isn't very rare but I may be wrong. Anyway now you should have your mask so enjoy it. Very useful when you are pulling in The Overthere (damn goons). It is also worth noting that if you click on a corpse by accident while sneaking and hiding you will become visible even if you get the "You may not loot this corpse at this time" message. This happened to me twice, both by accident. I would suggest not right clicking anything in there cause its easy to get yourself on a corpse run. Also I would like to thank Exeter, Wexxler, and Chitan for helping me out. Thats all.<br>&nbsp;<br>Spectix Blaize, 37 Druid of Drinal<br>Dekrypt, 11 Warrior of Drinal (on vacation)</td></tr>
