	   <tr><td colspan=2>Yep, you have crappy luck. Or maybe I just have incredible luck. I took two trips to lguk, never died. The first time the only other people in the zone were trying to get the mask themselves, so i looted all the corpses they left laying around and then left to do more important things. I made about 75pp or more just from looting their 'trash', so i didn't consider that trip a waste. I came back later when more people were likely to be in the zone. I shouted if anyone was on the assassin then asked him if i could have the mask if it dropped. He said wait in line because there was another rogue ahead of me who already asked. However, when the mask dropped, the other rogue was nowhere to be seen, so i got the mask. The rogue came back a few minutes later and said that he went LD, but congratulated me on my good luck. If you're careful, there's no way you'll die in lguk. The only mob that can see though hide are the sonic bats, but you don't even have to go near them. Go through the spider hallways and gargoyle room instead. Another thing to be careful of is getting out of the river on your way out. If you have sneak on, you won't have enough speed to get out of the water, unless you have sow, which is unlikely. My first time out i just turned sneak off and on again when i was on land; unfortunately, i didn't see the two ghoul shin knights behind me. Fortunately, i zoned just before they could kill me. The second time out i took a different approach. If there are baddies hanging around where you usually get out of the river, keep going to the waterfall room. While keeping sneak and hide on you can swim straight up the waterfall (only in EQ =P) and safely get out of the water onto one of the nearby rocks and from there down the path to the zone edge. Good luck,<br><br>Daviv McD &lt;Fearless Empire&gt;<br>24th rogue<br>Xegony<br>&nbsp;<br>Daviv McD 32nd Dwarf Rogue<br>Lords of Belterra<br>Xegony</td></tr>
